Project: Investigate a Dataset (Show and No Show of Patients for Medical Appointments)¶

Table of Contents¶

  • Introduction
  • Data Wrangling
  • Exploratory Data Analysis
  • Conclusions

Introduction¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment. A number of characteristics about the patient are included in each row. Our Task in here to import the data, cleand and analyze in order to get some facts about Show and No Show of Medical Appointment.

Context
A person makes a doctor appointment, receives all the instructions and no-show. Who to blame? If this help you studying or working, please dont forget to upvote :). Reference to Joni Hoppen and Aquarela Advanced Analytics Aquarela.

Content
110.527 medical appointments its 14 associated variables (characteristics). The most important one if the patient show-up or no-show to the appointment. Variable names are self-explanatory, if you have doubts, just let me know!

scholarship variable means this concept = https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolsa_Fam%C3%ADlia

14 variables

Data Dictionary:

  • PatientId: Identification of a patient
  • AppointmentID: Identification of each appointment
  • Gender:Male or Female . Female is the greater proportion, woman takes way more care of they health in comparison to man.
  • Age: How old is the patient.
  • AppointmentDay: In which Day the patient schedule a date.
  • ScheduledDay: tells us on what day the patient set up their appointment.
  • Neighborhood indicates the location of the hospital.
  • Neighbourhood: Where the appointment takes place.
  • Scholarship:True of False . Observation, this is a broad topic, consider reading this article https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolsa_Fam%C3%ADlia
  • Hipertension: 0 or 1.
  • Diabetes: 0 or 1.
  • Alcoholism: o or 1.
  • Handcap: The Handicap status from 0 to 4.
  • SMS_received: 1 or more messages sent to the patient.
  • No-show: True or False.
Inspiration:
What if that possible to predict someone to no-show an appointment?
Scope:
Our scope in this investigation is to Assess, Clean, Investigate The Data and retreive answers for below questions:
  • Research Question 1 (in General, regardless all other values, plot the percentage of Show and No-Show frequency!)
  • Research Question 2 (How The Gender Type impacts the Show and No Show Frequency and Percentage!)
  • Research Question3 (How The Scheduled Weekday impacts the Show and No Show Frequency and Percentage!)
  • Research Question 4 (How the Days difference between Appointment Day and Scheduled Day impacts the Show and No Show Frequency and Percentage!)
  • Research Question 5 (Highest City has the Most Show!)
  • Research Question 6 (How Scholarship impacts the Show and No Show Frequency and Percentage!)
  • Research Question 7 (How Diseases impacts the Show and No Show Frequency and Percentage!)
  • Research Question 8 (Does Handicap Grades affects the Show status!)
  • Research Question 9 (How Alcoholism Status impacts the Show and No Show Frequency and Percentage!)
  • Research Question 10 (Does Sending SMS to Patients affects the Show status!)
  • Research Question 11 (Average Age of Show and No Show!)

Quick Look and Summary for the Provided Data Set¶

from the data Frame info, we will notice the below:

  • Dataset has 14 coulmns.
  • Dataset has 110527 Rows
  • There are NAN values since all coulmns has 110527 non-null values (same number of Rows)
  • PatientId data type is Float64 (will need to be changed to string type is it is a unique value and should not be subject to any statistical or mathematical processing)
  • AppointmentID data type is Int64 (will need to be changed to string type is it is a unique value and should not be subject to any statistical or mathematical processing).
  • ScheduledDay and AppointmentDay are strings data type. will need to convert to datetime in order to be accessible.
  • Scholarship, Hipertension, Diabetes Alcoholism, SMS_recevied are int64 data types as values 0 or 1 for yes or no. need to convert to either boolean values (True or False) or String values (Yes or No) for better data understanding. will choose Yes or No String values in our data investigation.
  • Handcap status is int64 data type as values from 0 to 4 depending on the handicap status. will keep it as it is.
  • No-show data is tricky as No means show and Yes means No-Show. for better data understanding, will rename No to Show and Yes to No-Show.
  • Columns titles have a bit mistyping, so will do little changes with columns titles.

    • Now let's dig deeper into our dataset to identify the needed data cleaning before analysis and visualization.

#This function for plotting a Pie Shape Plot with Percentage and Show frequency values
def pie_plot(df_x, column, title):
    explode=[0.05]*df_x[column].nunique()
    df_x[column].value_counts().plot.pie(explode=explode, autopct='%1.1f%%',shadow=True,figsize=(10,8), legend=True)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()
    print(df_x[column].value_counts());
In [44]:
#this function for plotting different shape and type of columns based on Show and No Show values

def plot_col(df_x, column, title1, title2, title3):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,55)) 
    sns.set_style('whitegrid')
    
    explode=[0.05]*df_x[column].nunique()
    print(df_x[column].value_counts())
    df_x[column].value_counts().plot.pie(explode=explode, autopct='%1.1f%%',shadow=True,figsize=(10,8), legend=True)
    plt.title(title1)
    plt.show()
    

    print(df_x.groupby(['Show',column]).size())
    df_x.groupby(['Show',column]).size().sort_values().plot.bar(color=['tab:blue', 'tab:orange'], legend=False, rot=90);
    plt.title(title2)
    plt.ylabel=('Frequency')
    plt.show()
   

    new_df = df_x.groupby(column)['Show'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    new_df = new_df.mul(100).rename('Percent').reset_index().sort_values(column)
    g = sns.catplot(x=column, y='Percent', hue='Show', kind='bar', data=new_df)
    g.ax.set_ylim(0,100)
    g.fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)
    g.fig.suptitle(title3)
    print( new_df['Percent'])

Conclusions¶

From above Data investigation, we have tried to find out WHY we have Many Patients Not Showing at their Appointments and What factors make Patient No Show and what is the recommendation for that. There has been many data at provided dataset and we have selected some important factors but of course more data can be retreived by more investigation. From our answers to the Research Questions we have concluded the below findings:

  • Percentage of Patients not showing at their Scheduled Day is 20% which is considered high and need to be rectified
  • Saturday is the highest Patients Show percenatage at their appointments and less No Show and that's because of the Holiday
  • Tuesday has the Highest number of Patients applying for appointments, highest Number of Shows and highest number of no show. So hospital could limit the number of appointments at tuesday and move to Saturday
  • The Waiting days have a big impact to Patients to Show at their appointment. the less waiting days, the heighest number and percent of patients Showing at their appointments. So Most important to schedule close appointments as much as possible
  • Patients with Scholar Ship doesn't apppear to be more obligated to their appointments, and that's need more interest by giving them more options and facilities encouraging them to respect their appointments.
  • The Patients Diabetes only has the Lowest Show Frquency than those with hypertension. So we could do compaign to Patients have diabetes to increase their awarness
  • The Patients with Handicap Status 1 have the heighst Show Percentage then Status 2 comes next. for status with Handicap 3 and 4 has lowest percentage, seems they need more help for transportation for hospital. So we need to find some facilities help Handicap level 3 and 4 to help them Show at their appointments
  • A shocking result that Patients received SMS have a higher percenatge of No Show. need to evaluate and check how the SMS text shows, when it is been sent and what we can do to improve SMS
  • Percentage of Alcoholic Patients Show at Scheduled Day is lower Than percentage of Non-Alcoholic.
  • Average Age of Patients whom show at Apointment is 37.5 Years and Average Age of Patients whom No show at Apointment is 33.5 Years. So the older Patients the most frequent to their appointments. So need to increase awarness amongest young patients
